just_use lynrummy_elm.go

# label: SPIKE (lynrummy-elm-integration)
# role: supports feature — LynRummy Elm standalone client, reached through Gopher

V1 (2026-04-17). Serves the compiled Elm LynRummy client from
games/lynrummy/elm-port-docs/. Two routes:

- `/gopher/lynrummy-elm/` — HTML mount page with Gopher nav chrome.
- `/gopher/lynrummy-elm/elm.js` — serves the compiled bundle from
  disk. `ops/start` runs `elm make` before boot so the bundle is
  always fresh; if that fails, the handler returns a 404 pointing
  at the rebuild command.

V1 scope (tonight): standalone only — no auth, no server round-trip,
no real game state. The Elm client loads `Dealer.initialBoard` +
`Dealer.openingHand` and drag-drop operates purely client-side.

Next tier (not implemented): flags carrying player + game from
Gopher, HTTP-backed actions round-trip, SSE for opponent moves,
turn logic. See `showell/claude_writings/serving_from_gopher.md`
for the Part 2 plan.

Landing page link added to `views/helpers.go` under the Games
card. Findability = 10.
